-- `Ref` is the sole uppercase constructor that builds a mutable cell.
-- Generalizing `Ref x` would be unsound (write at one type, read at another).
-- This binding must NOT generalize — using it at two incompatible types must error.
-- The exclusion in isCtorAppHead is by the name "Ref" so it works regardless of
-- whether Ref is declared locally or comes from the stdlib prelude.
extern Ref : a -> Ref a
r = Ref (x => x)
-- Using r at two different function types in one tuple must produce a type error.
pair = ((r : Ref (Int -> Int)), (r : Ref (String -> String)))
